# Synapta AI Core — Standalone TypeScript Agent Engine

## Objectives
- Build `packages/synapta-ai-core/` as a normal, reusable TypeScript npm package that can be installed by Synapta and unrelated apps.
- Keep the core product-agnostic: provider connectivity, streaming, agents, sessions, context, skills, and a host-tool harness only.
- Define the structure for app-provided tools; do not ship Synapta business tools, shell tools, filesystem tools, or any default app tool set in the core package.
- Keep Synapta workflow catalogs, Phase A1 schemas, backend facades, and platform tools outside AI Core as host/app adapters.
- Use the least tooling possible: TypeScript, Node built-ins, native `fetch`, and small interfaces before new dependencies.

## Expected Outcome
- `packages/synapta-ai-core/` builds, typechecks, and tests as an independent npm package.
- Consumers can create an agent, create/resume sessions, stream LLM output, cancel work, and inspect session history.
- Consumers can register provider implementations and/or use a minimal OpenAI-compatible provider adapter.
- Consumers can register their own tools, context providers, and skills; AI Core dispatches only registered host tools.
- The package has no hard dependency on Synapta backend internals, protos, workflow catalogs, Svelte, APISIX, Keto, Temporal, NATS, database code, shell, or filesystem access.
- Synapta-specific catalog/tool integration is deferred to an app adapter after the generic core API is stable.

